# Delivery Pipeline

```
Architecture → Implementation → Documentation → QA → Code Review → Commit
```

## Artifacts (required per work item)

| Stage | File | Gate |
|-------|------|------|
| Architecture | `01-architecture.md` | Implementation approval |
| Implementation | `02-implementation.md` | Documenter entry |
| Documentation | `03-documentation.md` | PASS / FAIL / BLOCKED |
| QA | `04-qa-report.md` | PASS / FAIL / BLOCKED |
| Review | `05-code-review.md` | APPROVED / CHANGES_REQUESTED / BLOCKED |
| Commit | `06-commit-report.md` | hash + commitlint evidence |

Templates: `.ai/templates/`. Policy: `.ai/policies/delivery-pipeline.md`.

## Rules

- No stage skipping or self-approval.
- Documenter adds JSDoc + Mermaid before QA.
- QA must run `npm run lint` and `npm run format:check` (when frontend exists).
- Committer must pass commitlint (Conventional Commits).
- FAIL/CHANGES_REQUESTED → Implementation or Documenter; BLOCKED → Architecture.
